      • defineEdge

        public void defineEdge​(java.lang.Integer v1,
                       java.lang.Integer v2,
                       java.lang.Integer weight)
        Defines a new edge in the graph. This method assume correct input (no loops, no multi-edges) and is used for the construction of the initial graph. The edge is assigned a unique identifier.
        Parameters:
        v1 - first endpoint
        v2 - second endpoint
        weight - weight of the edge

      • addEdge

        public void addEdge​(java.lang.Integer v1,
                    java.lang.Integer v2,
                    java.lang.Integer weight,
                    java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> id)
        Adds an edge to the graph. This method is used for modifications of a graph already read from input. If there is already an existing edge, the lighter one is kept. Loops are not added. The edge is assigned a new identifier.
        Parameters:
        v1 - first endpoint
        v2 - second endpoint
        weight - weight of the edge
        id - edge identifier
